This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as it deals with the development of an Intrusion Detection System (IDS) to secure computer networks. It may also belong to the sub-category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it deals with the analysis of network data. Additionally, it may belong to the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) as it deals with the analysis of network motifs. The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques to identify attack scenarios, which may place it in the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
